{
  "stem": "3360.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- then I remember when we moved from a smaller place to a little larger place.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had just received a new, a new doll buggy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we walked-- the moving was done by whatever truck, I don't recall that-- but my mother and I walked from the one place where we lived to the new place.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was just practically jumping with joy behind that new buggy and the doll was tucked in under the cover.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when we arrived at this new apartment, which was 24 [GERMAN] in Hamburg, I, I, I experienced what was probably my very first encounter with anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My mother, when she approached the entrance, turned all shades of white.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, she just got as white as a sheet.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she had seen where our name had been newly fastened to the side of the entrance, where all the names were etched, that somebody had taken a, a crayon or whatever-- it was black-- and painted swastikas over our name.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that was truly, I guess, my very first-- this was in 1930-- and that was my very first encounter with anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we actually lived in that apartment for about four years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we-- I did find some very nice little friends there, and I had a fairly normal life.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There-",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, I was five years old.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I entered school at six, and walked from there to my school in the Kielort Allee, which was the grade school from first through fourth grade.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can you spell the name of that school?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "K-I-E-L-O-R-T and Allee is like-- A-L-L-E-E.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's actually a French word, but it's named-- it's used in Germany frequently for street.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Instead of street, it's allee, like avenue, something like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
